State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Ancient Nordic Sentinels are a type of gigantic Foundation Stone Golem made of old norse architecture. Guardians of the ancient tombs, and the terror of their invaders, these fearsome colossi animated by the souls of powerful warriors will crush all foes with no mercy.
State.Name: Ancient Nordic Sentinel- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''golem'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: In ancient times, dating as far back as the Meretich Era, groups of honorable, strong, and proud men raised their weapons against the tyranny of the Dragons in Skyrim, when almost everyone else still saw them as powerful gods to be venerated. With the return of the Dragons, these revenants rose from their tombs to resume their missions.
State.Name: Ancient Skeletons- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ash Golems are enhanced, more brute-force oriented versions of the Ash Guardians. These 4-armed golems are formed from Red Mountain's ashes, and are crafted with a rune-covered magic chest belt containing a Heart Stone, which avoids the risk of summoning an uncontrolled construct, as can happen with common Ash Guardians.
State.Name: Ash Golem- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''atronach'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Crystal Golems are large masses of faceless and vaguely humanoid crystal, animated by unknown means, that patrol Blackreach. Despite Azura's Moonshadow and Meridia's Colored Rooms being almost inaccessible to mortals, it's certain that some roam that realms since they're often summoned on Nirn by azura's and meridia's worshipers.
State.Name: Crystal Golems - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dark souls'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ages ago, they were the valiant chivalric members of Nord society, who fought bravely in battle to protect their cities and temples, but today, due to the downfall of the Dragon Cult, they trudge around in their decaying forms, astride their cadaverous steeds, a feeble, insane shadow of their former selves.
State.Name: Draugr Cavalry- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''undead'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Dwarven Colossus are one of the magnum opus amongst the Dwemer Animunculi. Massive, and with incredible endurance and fire power, these machines possess specialized weapons on their arms, a large dual-blade gauntlet on the right and a hammer piston that creates fire pulses on the left. They are also able to breath extremely destructive fire.
State.Name: Dwarven Colossus - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dwemer'')

State.Author: lifestorock and jackstarr
State.Description: Skyrim Immersive Creatures adds dozens of new creatures to enhance your gaming experience. This mod adds brand new creatures which fit in to the world of Skyrim, alongside variations of existing creatures, adding diversity and improving gameplay.
State.Name: Skyrim Immersive Creatures Special Edition

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Created to be the pawns on the front line of the Dwemer army, Dwarven Defenders are articulated automatons designed to emulate the combat skills of their creators in wars and conflicts. Wielding light dwarven shields, and sledgehammers, and firing blasts of electricity through their central chest core, these machine armies are a force to be feared.
State.Name: Dwarven Defenders- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dwemer'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Goblins are violent and primitive small orc-kin humanoids found throughout Tamriel, often living in sewers, caves, cluttered camps and ruins, in small clan-based societies. Accompanied by their tamed Durzogs, they are known for making their camps near roads to rob travelers. Goblins are sentient, and worship Malacath.
State.Name: Goblins- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Ice Jötun is one of the now rarely seen, and almost mythological Titan breeds. He has blue skin, an ugly, deformed face covered in warts, and long snow-covered hair and beard. The body is robust and wrinkled, and the arms are long and end in large hands. The feet are also powerful, being able to crush a bear with a single stomp.
State.Name: Ice Titans- Mihail Monsters and Animals (LE version) (''witcher'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: It's easy to summarize a Mimic: they disguise themselves as chests, waiting for victims to try to open them. When a wretch tries to do so, the Mimic will attack the victim with its long sharp claws and try to bite the poor soul with a large mouth full of sharp teeth, a bite so powerful that it is often described as causing instant death.
State.Name: Chest Mimics- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dark souls'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ogrims are a type of ogre-like enormous daedra with very little intellect and enormous raw power. They are sent into the mortal world to menace living things for the amusement of the Daedric Princes, and are mostly associated with Malacath. Many scholars even speculate them to be a daedric corruption of the Ogres made by Malacath himself.
State.Name: Ogrim- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''daedra'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Sea Giants are a mysterious and little-understood race of seafaring giants, who tirelessly engage in piracy in the Sea of Ghosts region, sailing their large ships decorated with giant bones and totems. They are also known as skilled whalers.
State.Name: Sea Giants - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Storm Golems are the elite among other electricity-based atronachs. They appear to be formed from containing a Storm Atronach through magical bracelets, which force it into a more humanoid form, while causing its power to build up in its core, causing tremendous energy concentration, elevating the golem to levels above any other Storm Atronach.
State.Name: Storm Golem- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''atronach'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Thri-Kreen are mutated ritualistic warriors created by Falmer alchemy using the Chaurus creature as a base. These obedient humanoid insects outperform the own Falmers in physical capacities, and do not need to rest, being excellent defenders of the hives where they live. They are also commonly used to protect the valuable Shellbugs.
State.Name: Thri-Kreen Warriors and Shellbugs- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)(''falmer'')

State.Author: Mihail Romanov
State.Description: Most undead werewolves have had their bodies resurrected and their souls forcibly bound to them again by dark wizards such as the Hagraven, using dark magic to make the beasts loyal servants. Unable to enter the promised afterlife, they are now doomed to wander the world as decaying werewolf corpses rather than traveling to the Hunting Grounds.
State.Name: Undead Werewolves - Mihail Monsters and Animals (LE version)

In appearance, Zombies are usually naked, rotting bodies exhibiting severe injuries, and compound fractures, they are covered in maggot infestations and their smell is nauseating and can be detected long before they are even spotted.
State.Name: Zombies- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''undead'')
